                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="197994" author="doug" created="Sat, 3 Jun 2017 03:24:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Whenever I ask questions about the RDMA API, I am told it is not documented so just do what the iSer driver does. &#160;Sigh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;James: would you agree that we should &quot;duplicate&quot; the iSer driver&apos;s iser_memory.c approach to differentiating between fmr and fastreg and how it makes use of the new RDMA calls? &#160;Doing this would get us away from being &quot;so different&quot; from the other RDMA users who all seem to just copy iSer anyway. &#160;We would keep our existing runtime model (i.e. our scheduler), but would get us to use the RDMA data structures in exactly the same way as iSer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
